xxl.relational
Class FileResultSet

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--xxl.relational.AbstractResultSet
        |
        +--xxl.relational.FileResultSet
public class FileResultSet
extends AbstractResultSet

This class constructs a ResultSet for a given File.

The first line of the file must contain all the column names delimited by a character of columnDelimiters. The default columnDelimiters are "\t".

The second line of the file must contain the column types (also delimited by columnDelimiters). There are two possible column types: NUMBER and VARCHAR. The type Varchar is set to Varchar(40) by default.

The third line of the file is an empty line.

The first three lines of the file are case insensitive. All following lines are case sensitive.

Each of the following lines represents a tuple of this relation.
Values are delimited by the characters of columnDelimiters.
To model a SQL-Null-Value one must use the nullRepresentation. The String nullRepresentation is by default set to "#".

Example for a file: 


	key     NAME        first name  year of birth
	Number  Varchar     varChar     number

	1       Tiger       Scott       1957
	2       Smith       Scott       1961
	3       Smith       John        1948
	4       #           Test        #
By passing the file name to the constructor, the specified file can be used as a ResultSet.
